nections may allow third parties to collect or share data about you. We do not control these third-party websites or applications or platforms and are not responsible for their privacy statements or terms and conditions.</p></li></ol><p><strong><br></strong></p><ol start="7"><li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: decimal;" data-mce-style="list-style-type: decimal;"><p dir="ltr" role="presentation">This Privacy Policy together with all other policies of the Website including Terms of Use or any other policy that the Website from time to time publish or provide forms an integral part of the functioning of the Website and shall be read together. We therefore request and encourage you to read this Privacy Policy together with the other policies of the Website.&nbsp;</p></li></ol><p><strong><br></strong></p><ol start="8"><li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: decimal;" data-mce-style="list-style-type: decimal;"><p dir="ltr" role="presentation"><strong>Information being collected:</strong></p></li><li style="list-style-type: none;" data-mce-style="list-style-type: none;"><ol><li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;" data-mce-style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"><p dir="ltr" role="presentation">We may collect information from Users at various stages from [registration on the Website by the Users to submission of content by the Users or while the User is accessing or viewing or browsing the Website or using any Services]. The information collected may be personally identifiable information or other information. You may choose to not provide the information if You do not wish to use the Website and/or Services. All information, disclosed by you shall be deemed to be disclosed willingly and without any coercion.</p></li></ol></li></ol><p><strong><br></strong></p><ol start="9"><li style="list-style-type: none;" data-mce-style="list-style-type: none;"><ol start="2"><li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;" data-mce-style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"><p dir="ltr" role="presentation">We may collect, use and share personal information that identifies You in a variety of ways, including, but not limited to the information submitted during download, installation and/or use/access of the Website or in connection with access/use of Services or features offered through the Website or in connection with the Website. "Personal information" of a person means any information which, either directly or indirectly, in combination with other information available or likely to be available is capable of identifying such person. To avail certain Services on the Website, the User would be required to provide certain personal information including (but not limited to) [Your name, image, mailing address, email address, phone number, username, password, occupation, nationality, credit/debit card details, <span class="mce-spellchecker-annotation mce-spellchecker-word mce-cram_889271250531604583398432" aria-invalid="spelling" data-mce-highlight-id="mce-cram_889271250531604583398432" data-mce-bogus="1" data-mce-annotation="postcode" data-mce-lingo="en_us">postcode</span>, date, time or place of birth, etc.. We collect such personal information of the User only if the User voluntarily submit such information to us or provide access to such information by connecting to social networking sites through the Website or Services (for example when You use the facilities or Services connected with the Website or engage in certain Website related activities including but not limited to becoming a member or signing up for an account or linking an account through a social network including, but not limited to Facebook, Twitter, Google Plus, and/or LinkedIn).] We may also collect personal information from the User when corresponding with us by e-mail or phone, or to access/use any other interactive/non-interactive features of the Website and/or Services and the same is voluntarily provided by the User. As mentioned above, the User can always refuse to provide personal information, however such refusal or subsequent withdrawal, may prevent the User from using the Website, and/or certain features of the Website and Services.</p></li></ol></li></ol><p><strong><br></strong></p><ol start="9"><li style="list-style-type: none;" data-mce-style="list-style-type: none;"><ol start="3"><li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;" data-mce-style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"><p dir="ltr" role="presentation">We may collect non-personal information from the User whenever the User use, access, view, visit, browse or interact with the Website and/or use any Services. Non-personal information may include the mobile or computer’s name, version, the type of device used, users’ operating system and version, the unique ID of the mobile device, third-party apps or websites or services that referred to the User on the Website, language preferences, location information, IP address, technical information, information about third-party apps including without limitation package name (which is same as the package id on play store), package version, installation and/or uninstallation event information and other similar information about the User.</p></li></ol></li></ol><p><strong><br></strong></p><ol start="9"><li style="list-style-type: none;" data-mce-style="list-style-type: none;"><ol start="4"><li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;" data-mce-style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"><p dir="ltr" role="presentation">We may also collect aggregated data such as statistical or demographic data for any purpose. Aggregated data could be derived from the personal information of the User but is not considered personal information or sensitive personal data or information in law as this data will not directly or indirectly reveal the identity of the User. For example, we may aggregate your usage data to calculate the percentage of users accessing a specific Website feature. However, if we combine or connect aggregated data with the